			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I'm about at 50% success. Most of my successes have come when my group is all or mostly Guild Members. I think because we all know each others playing style and work well together. I think class is not the major issue, though you obviously wouldn't want 6 of the same class, but wether the player behind the class plays well. I know its pretty much impossible to tell how good someone is if you've never grouped with them before but if you have a choice I would suggest grouping with people you know and trust. A mezzer and/or slower is not necessary at all. I have won without either. I think they probably make it worse because people rely on them too much. 
<br />

<br />
I think Pallies are probably the best pullers Not because they Pac pull but because they have that option. A Pally that pac's every mob isn't doing you any favors but when they know when to pac to prevent too many adds I think they are the best pullers in LDoN. I have heard Bard's are good pullers but haven't grouped with one in LDoN yet.
<br />

<br />
My biggest complaint about the new spells is Spirit of the Shrew. I don't think anyone needs to run fast in LDoN zones. If you are running you are losing IMHO. I think an indoor Harmony(i.e. Pacify) would have been way more useful. I use Harmony of nature when pulling outdoors alot and I love it. 
<br />

<br />
When I pull in LDoN I almost always die but I almost always win the adventure at the same time. Usually if I pull too many to handle I do as much damage as I can before I die(I think an AE Jolt would be nice, hehe*see spell complaints above*) and then run back while my group finishes the job. I'm not saying this is a preferred strategy and is by no means intentional but it has worked for me, LOL.
<br />

<br />
and like was said earlier FOCUS on what you need to do. Don't whine or worry about what happened just keep moving. I have been in adventures that have started off very badly, i.e. premature zoning without buffing and/or wipes and still succeed. 90 minutes is plenty of time if things are done right. 
<br />

<br />
and finally remember complacency kills. When you start getting lazy towards the end of the adventure (i.e. sloppy pulling or not refreshing key buffs that have faded) that can be detrimental.<br />_________________<br />Tohvaks Silverglade
<br />
59 Outrider of Karana
<br />
&lt;Champions of Divinity&gt;
<br />
Tunare Server</span><span class="gentblsmall"></span></td>
