			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Before going in get to know your team and who plays what role.  I've found the traditional EQ group roles are useless in LDoN. I had to have my mage tell the chanter to take a chill pill and relax on 2 mob pulls. My earthie was more than capable of handling one critter while other was getting pummelled by main group.  When group was ready, they finished off what was left.  Chanter got no aggro and we could double pull.  LDoN seems to be designed for each class to shine especially bright in their special talent catagory. My ranger is a damage dealing seeker who can tell you if a boss is up or not.  Best advice is think of what each class is best at and how that fits into a stradegy for the whole group. Think you'll find there are all kinds of fun combinations to be tried.</span><span class="gentblsmall"></span></td>
