			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">My experiences in LDON have been interesting to put it mildly.
<br />

<br />
For now, I have given up all hope for pickup groups.  I may have one or two people as pickups, but I've had a few bad experiences with the pickup groups.
<br />

<br />
A Shaman who wouldn't meditate, wouldn't slow, barely healed, all he wanted to do was DOT and Melee.  Several times he interrupted the puller's bow shots and pulled on his own (eventually his attitude pushed the wizard to leave, then he got dropped from the group by the leader after more trouble.  So he tried to train the group, but our chanter was on top of him, mezzing everything he could bring.)
<br />

<br />
A Druid who insisted we do obscure randoms on every no drop, basically because she presumed everyone but her was some kind of cheater that would hack their randoms to win.  This person was the designated looter, so we played along.  Then as soon as the mission was successful (assassination as I recall) there was a sudden claim that Mom was going to pull the plug.  Someone suggested at least splitting the cash.   The druid then said "Catch me next time I'm on for your split," and went Linkdead.
<br />

<br />
Additionally, I've had one other instance of the looter absconding with everything.  One of a group leader who felt that we needed to kill everything down every dead end before making our way to the rescue target (even though more than half the zone was between us and the target)  kept telling the group not to worry about adds or calming before pulls because "we have a chanter" but lays a DOT on every mob, and runs off pulling other mobs to root-park and dot while the group is dealing with the existing pull.  (at the time I was the enchanter) Eventually I stopped trying to mez anything, since everything was dot'd.  Instead I focused on hasting the melees, clarity for the healer and other caster, and lots of Berserker Strength spells for the main tank (minor rune without the gem component).
<br />

<br />
On the other hand, my experiences with guild based LDON groups have been extremely successful.  Whether 3 person or 6 person or anywhere in between.  We communicate.  We count on each other.  We know our jobs and follow through!
<br />

<br />
I've never had a looter disappear on a guild LDON.  I've never had group infighting on a guild LDON.  There are a few people outside my guild I'll gladly join forces with, but for the most part, pickup groups are out for me right now.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=852643" target="_blank" class="postlink">Dharisk</a>
<br />
Ranger of Tunare (deity and server)</span><span class="gentblsmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
